-- Bharati Shipyard in Talks With Shipping Corp. to Sell a Stake, Kumar Says
-- B y   S u e   L i n g   C h a n
-- 2010-09-28T08:27:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-28/bharati-shipyard-in-talks-with-shipping-corp-to-sell-a-stake-kumar-says.html
Bharati Shipyard Ltd. is in talks
with Shipping Corp. of India Ltd. to sell as much as a 15
percent stake, Vijay Kumar, managing director of the Indian
shipbuilder, spoke in an interview in Singapore today.  “We are interested and we have been discussing with them
for the last one year,” Kumar said. “We would like it to be
partly current shares and partly new shares.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sue Ling Chan in Singapore at 
 slchan@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
